            <div type="translation">
                <ab>
                <lb n="1"/>To <persName ref="http://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/brill-s-new-pauly/platorius-e927310">Aulus Platorius Nepos, son of Aulus,
                <lb n="2"/>from the (family) Sergia 
                <lb n="3"/>Aponius Italicus Manilianus,
                <lb n="4"/>Caius Licinius Pollio</persName>
                <lb n="5"/>Consul, Augur
                <lb n="6"/>Envoy of the Emperor of the 
                <lb n="7"/><placeName>Provenance of Britania</placeName> 
                <lb n="8"/>Envoy of the Emperor of the 
                <lb n="9"/><placeName>Provenance of Germania the Lower</placeName> 
                <lb n="10"/>Envoy of the Emperor of the <placeName>Provenance Thrace</placeName> 
                <lb n="11"/>Lieutenant-general of <orgName>the First Legion, Adiutrix</orgName> 
                <lb n="12"/>Quaestor <note>Originally two deputies of the consuls, to investigate and try capital crimes. Their number was gradually increased to 40. Most were employed in the provinces. See: <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0060%3Aentry%3Dquaestor">Charlton T. Lewis, An Elementary Latin Dictionary</ref> </note> of the <placeName>provenance of Macedonia</placeName>, 
                <lb n="13"/>Overseer of the roads: <placeName>Cassia</placeName>, <placeName>Clodia</placeName> 
                <lb n="14"/><placeName>Ciminia</placeName>, [and] <placeName>the New Trajan</placeName>; 
                <lb n="15"/>Candidate of the divine <persName>Trajan</persName>, 
                <lb n="16"/>Tribune of the army of <orgName>Fortune's <note>Literally firstborn.</note> XXII Legion</orgName>
                <lb n="17"/>(the pius, the faithful)
                <lb n="18"/>Chief tribune of the people, a member of the <orgName>triumvir capitales</orgName>,
                <lb n="19"/>Protector, 
                <lb n="20"/>by means of decree of members of the municipal senate.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p><emph>"For these I set no limits, world or time, But make a gift of empire without end."--Virgil, the Aenied</emph></p>
               
                
